;; mark_setter_skew.synth — mark-setter candidate via distance
;; skew at a CS ivar (issue 007, July 2026 round).
;;
;; Companion to mark_distance_skew.synth: same
;; same-key-different-distance trick, but the skew lands on
;; t.data (a CS-contour ivar) instead of an ES formal, so
;; stage 2's ES-formal/return qualifier skips it and control
;; falls through to stage 4, which collects CS marked
;; confluences and computes AKIND_MARK setters for them.
;; t.data is NOT a type confluence (both writes int32), so
;; stage 3 never touches it; the seed type confluence lives on
;; u.tag (int32+float32), which stages 1-3 can't act on.
;; CS_T has two defs (t@main, o@g) with different mark-setter
;; views (t sees both writes, o only the long-path one).
;;
;; Golden documents what actually fires.

shape: mark_setter_skew
